msgid "Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:4
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A simple Weex page sample is just a piece of `<template>` code, a piece of "
"`<style>` code and a piece of `<script>` code. The three parts together "
"describe a whole Weex page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:8
msgid ""
"`<template>`: *required*. Just uses HTML syntax and describes the structure "
"of a Weex page, which is build upon several tags. Each tag means a type of "
"*component*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:8
msgid ""
"`<style>`: *optional*. Describes the presetation details, and the content is "
"based on CSS syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:8
msgid ""
"`<script>`: *optional*. Describes the data and behaiver with JavaScript "
"syntax. It defines data and how these data are processed etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```html\n"
"<template>\n"
"  <!-- (required) the structure of page -->\n"
"</template>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<style>\n"
"  /* (optional) stylesheet */\n"
"</style>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<script>\n"
"  /* (optional) the definition of data, methods and life-circle */\n"
"</script>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "`<template>`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We describe page structure in `<template>` tag like the following "
"definition:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```html\n"
"<template>\n"
"  <container>\n"
"    <image style=\"width: 200; height: 200;\" "
"src=\"http://gtms02.alicdn.com/tps/i2/TB1QHKjMXXXXXadXVXX20ySQVXX-512-512.png\"></image>\n"
"    <text>Alibaba Weex Team</text>\n"
"  </container>\n"
"</template>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:37
msgid ""
"Here `container` tag is the root element of the component. `image` tag "
"describes a picture, while `text` tag means a paragraph of text."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:39
msgid ""
"Just similar to HTML, each component could have its own attributes, some "
"components also have children as their sub components."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:41
msgid ""
"The root element of template: In a `template` tag, there could be only one "
"root component which has no display logics directive. Here are three types "
"of root component we support now:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:45
msgid "`<container>`: a common native container"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:45
msgid "`<scroller>`: a native scroll view"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:45
msgid "`<list>`: a native cell-reusable list view"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:47
msgid "Only these type of components are allowed for root element."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:49
msgid "[See all built-in components](../components/README.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "`<style>`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:53
msgid ""
"You can consider the Weex style syntax is a subset of the CSS syntax, but "
"there is still some differences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First we could write inline `style` attribute in `<template>` "
"element. Second we could use the `class` attribute to apply stylesheets, "
"which are defined with single-class selectors in `<style>` code. Here is an "
"example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:63
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```html\n"
"<template>\n"
"  <container>\n"
"    <text style=\"font-size: 64;\">Alibaba</text>\n"
"    <text class=\"large\">Weex Team</text>\n"
"  </container>\n"
"</template>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<style>\n"
"  .large {font-size: 64;}\n"
"</style>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:70
msgid ""
"Both the two `text` components above have the same `font-size`, which is "
"`64` pixel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:72
msgid "[See common styles in Weex](../references/common-style.md)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "`<script>`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:76
msgid ""
"The syntax is JavaScript (ES5) and it describes data and behavior of a Weex "
"page. Here we create three paragraphs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```html\n"
"<template>\n"
"  <container>\n"
"    <text>The time is {{datetime}}</text>\n"
"    <text>{{title}}</text>\n"
"    <text>{{getTitle()}}</text>\n"
"  </container>\n"
"</template>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<script>\n"
"  module.exports = {\n"
"    data: {\n"
"      title: 'Alibaba',\n"
"      date: null\n"
"    },\n"
"    methods: {\n"
"      getTitle: function () {\n"
"        return 'Weex Team'\n"
"      }\n"
"    },\n"
"    created: function() {\n"
"      this.datetime = new Date().toLocaleString()\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"</script>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dev/download/weex_doc/weex/doc/_book/syntax/README.md:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This piece of `<script>` code will generate some component options and "
"assign it to `module.exports`. The three text components above respectively "
"shows the current datetime, 'Alibaba' and 'Weex Team'. The `data` in the "
"`<script>` code stores component data which could be used for "
"[data-binding](./data-binding.md) in the `<template>`. When data changes, "
"the bound value will be updated automatically. Also it could be read and "
"written by `this.x` in its methods.\n"
msgstr ""

